description: Imagine that imaginary friends were real. Now imagine that IF director John Krasinski and star Ryan Reynolds convinced A-list pals to voice them.
title: 'IF' only! These imaginary friends are sweet, but could have been so much more

description: The rapper slipped free from the legal mess that swallowed his label and his mentor Young Thug — but on his new album, he's still in the grip of an unending image crisis.
title: On 'One of Wun,' Gunna can't flaunt his way out of the YSL trial's shadow

description: Wallace is known for his celebrity profiles, but his new memoir, Another Word For Love, is about his own life, growing up unhoused, Black and queer, and getting his start as a writer at the age of 40.
title: Writer Carvell Wallace on past pain and forgiveness: Letting go is 'always available'

description: People who live near the areas where nuclear weapons were tested say their communities still suffer harm and are pressing Congress to renew funding to help them.
title: Those sickened by U.S. nuclear testing program take their fight to Congress

description: The opinion was written by Justice Clarence Thomas, who reversed the decision of the 5th Circuit. Justices Neil Gorsuch and Samuel Alito dissented.
title: Supreme Court upholds funding structure for CFPB
